text: Dreamt I was in nightclub, in winter, in only a t-shirt. I got bored and walked off into the night, down to the river. In the very far horizon, somewhere behind the water, the sky was clear and light blue, like the sun was waiting for the morning, still submerged in the river.

I was surprised as it was 4 AM, now I realize the only possible way for this to make sense is I was somehow in the North, where winter sun lingers forever. A lot of smoke was coming up from the river and around it, from the sewers. I observed it. The faint light illuminated well

Proceeded to walk through a street-tunnel, a lot of drunk drivers and motorbikers like to speed through it, the sidewalk is narrow, kept looking behind me and hugging the wall when someone was coming, two-hundred miles per hour cars touching barely my shoulder. I have done this.

It was very cold, but I feel my body burning alcohol to keep me warm, as it tends to do. Wondered if the people in the club missed me. In the centre there was a Christmas bazaar, I walked around and went home. Went to bed, slept a bit. Woke up to post this, will now have coffee
